    <div id="artwork-details">
    <div id="tombstone">

    <p>    Boris Nikolaevich Shirokorad<br />
(Born Belgorod region of Kursk, 1907; died 1988)<br />
Sergei Dmitrievich Spasskii<br />
(Born Kiev, 1898; died near Iaroslavl, 1956)<br />
    </p>
    <h3><em>A Terrible Ghost</em>, TASS No. 0901, February 4, 1944</h3>

    <p>
    Stencil<br />    1670 x 869 mm<br />    February 2 is the anniversary of the defeat of the German Fascist forces at Stalingrad.<br />
<br />
Hitler can’t sleep. Through the darkness<br />
A skeleton appears to him.<br />
Goosebumps rise on his skin.<br />
“Remember, Hitler, Stalingrad!<br />
We died there a year ago – <br />
Soon the same will happen to you!”<br />    Gift of the USSR Society for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, 2010.161</p>
        
        <!--<p id="dept-gallery">--><!--<br />-->
         <!--</p>-->
    </p>
    </div><!--/tombstone-->

